  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1666711627519-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1666711627519-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1666711627519-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1666711627519-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1666711627519-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a medium sized pot over a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>sliced onion</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1666711632039-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1666711632039-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1666711632039-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1666711632039-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1666711632039-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is softening, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>chopped creamed</strong> <strong>coconut </strong>in 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your<strong> coconut stock</strong></p><p>Drain your <strong>green</strong> <strong>lentils</strong>, then rinse them together with your<strong> red lentils</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1666711636149-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1666711636149-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1666711636149-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1666711636149-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1666711636149-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>curry powder</strong> to the pot and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>rinsed</strong> <strong>lentils </strong>and <strong>coconut</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and cook for 15-20 min or until all the stock is absorbed and the lentils are tender – this is your <strong>mixed lentil</strong> <strong>dal</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1666711641298-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1666711641298-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1666711641298-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1666711641298-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1666711641298-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the dal is cooking, heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>chicken breast strips </strong>into smaller strips</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken strips</strong> and <strong>remaining sliced onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong> and cook for 10-12 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>pan-fried chicken & onion</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1666711646628-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1666711646628-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1666711646628-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1666711646628-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1666711646628-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and roughly chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and roughly chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1666711650799-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1666711650799-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1666711650799-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1666711650799-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1666711650799-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Grind the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped ginger</strong> in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> until you're left with a smooth paste</p><p>Add<strong> </strong>the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>, your <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> to the paste and mix it all together – this is your <strong>coriander chutney</strong></p><p>Tip: If you don't have a pestle & mortar, chop everything very finely</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1666711655466-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1666711655466-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1666711655466-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1666711655466-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1666711655466-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>mixed lentil</strong> <strong>dal</strong> topped with the <strong>pan-fried</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>&</strong> <strong>onion</strong></p><p>Dollop the <strong>coriander chutney</strong> all over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
